59 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_HEAP_SNAPSHOT_VERIFY
60 class HeapEntryVerifier {
61  public:
62  HeapEntryVerifier(HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator, Tagged<HeapObject> obj)
63  : generator_(generator),
64  primary_object_(obj),
65  reference_summary_(
66  ReferenceSummary::SummarizeReferencesFrom(generator->heap(), obj)) {
67  generator->set_verifier(this);
68  }
69  ~HeapEntryVerifier() {
70  CheckAllReferencesWereChecked();
71  generator_->set_verifier(nullptr);
72  }
73 
74  // Checks that `host` retains `target`, according to the marking visitor. This
75  // allows us to verify, when adding edges to the snapshot, that they
76  // correspond to real retaining relationships.
77  void CheckStrongReference(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
78  Tagged<HeapObject> target) {
79  // All references should be from the current primary object.
80  CHECK_EQ(host, primary_object_);
81 
82  checked_objects_.insert(target);
83 
84  // Check whether there is a direct strong reference from host to target.
85  if (reference_summary_.strong_references().find(target) !=
86  reference_summary_.strong_references().end()) {
87  return;
88  }
89 
90  // There is no direct reference from host to target, but sometimes heap
91  // snapshots include references that skip one, two, or three objects, such
92  // as __proto__ on a JSObject referring to its Map's prototype, or a
93  // property getter that bypasses the property array and accessor info. At
94  // this point, we must check for those indirect references.
95  for (size_t level = 0; level < 3; ++level) {
96  const UnorderedHeapObjectSet& indirect =
97  GetIndirectStrongReferences(level);
98  if (indirect.find(target) != indirect.end()) {
99  return;
100  }
101  }
102 
103  FATAL("Could not find any matching reference");
104  }
105 
106  // Checks that `host` has a weak reference to `target`, according to the
107  // marking visitor.
108  void CheckWeakReference(Tagged<HeapObject> host, Tagged<HeapObject> target) {
109  // All references should be from the current primary object.
110  CHECK_EQ(host, primary_object_);
111 
112  checked_objects_.insert(target);
113  CHECK_NE(reference_summary_.weak_references().find(target),
114  reference_summary_.weak_references().end());
115  }
116 
117  // Marks the relationship between `host` and `target` as checked, even if the
118  // marking visitor found no such relationship. This is necessary for
119  // ephemerons, where a pair of objects is required to retain the target.
120  // Use this function with care, since it bypasses verification.
121  void MarkReferenceCheckedWithoutChecking(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
122  Tagged<HeapObject> target) {
123  if (host == primary_object_) {
124  checked_objects_.insert(target);
125  }
126  }
127 
128  // Verifies that all of the references found by the marking visitor were
129  // checked via a call to CheckStrongReference or CheckWeakReference, or
130  // deliberately skipped via a call to MarkReferenceCheckedWithoutChecking.
131  // This ensures that there aren't retaining relationships found by the marking
132  // visitor which were omitted from the heap snapshot.
133  void CheckAllReferencesWereChecked() {
134  // Both loops below skip pointers to read-only objects, because the heap
135  // snapshot deliberately omits many of those (see IsEssentialObject).
136  // Read-only objects can't ever retain normal read-write objects, so these
137  // are fine to skip.
138  for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj : reference_summary_.strong_references()) {
139  if (!MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
140  CHECK_NE(checked_objects_.find(obj), checked_objects_.end());
141  }
142  }
143  for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj : reference_summary_.weak_references()) {
144  if (!MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
145  CHECK_NE(checked_objects_.find(obj), checked_objects_.end());
146  }
147  }
148  }
149 
150  private:
151  using UnorderedHeapObjectSet =
152  std::unordered_set<Tagged<HeapObject>, Object::Hasher,
153  Object::KeyEqualSafe>;
154 
155  const UnorderedHeapObjectSet& GetIndirectStrongReferences(size_t level) {
156  CHECK_GE(indirect_strong_references_.size(), level);
157 
158  if (indirect_strong_references_.size() == level) {
159  // Expansion is needed.
160  indirect_strong_references_.resize(level + 1);
161  const UnorderedHeapObjectSet& previous =
162  level == 0 ? reference_summary_.strong_references()
163  : indirect_strong_references_[level - 1];
164  for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj : previous) {
165  if (MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
166  // Marking visitors don't expect to visit objects in read-only space,
167  // and will fail DCHECKs if they are used on those objects. Read-only
168  // objects can never retain anything outside read-only space, so
169  // skipping those objects doesn't weaken verification.
170  continue;
171  }
172 
173  // Indirect references should only bypass internal structures, not
174  // user-visible objects or contexts.
175  if (IsJSReceiver(obj) || IsString(obj) || IsContext(obj)) {
176  continue;
177  }
178 
179  ReferenceSummary summary =
180  ReferenceSummary::SummarizeReferencesFrom(generator_->heap(), obj);
181  indirect_strong_references_[level].insert(
182  summary.strong_references().begin(),
183  summary.strong_references().end());
184  }
185  }
186 
187  return indirect_strong_references_[level];
188  }
189 
190  DISALLOW_GARBAGE_COLLECTION(no_gc)
191  HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator_;
192  Tagged<HeapObject> primary_object_;
193 
194  // All objects referred to by primary_object_, according to a marking visitor.
195  ReferenceSummary reference_summary_;
196 
197  // Objects that have been checked via a call to CheckStrongReference or
198  // CheckWeakReference, or deliberately skipped via a call to
199  // MarkReferenceCheckedWithoutChecking.
200  std::unordered_set<Tagged<HeapObject>, Object::Hasher, Object::KeyEqualSafe>
201  checked_objects_;
202 
203  // Objects transitively retained by the primary object. The objects in the set
204  // at index i are retained by the primary object via a chain of i+1
205  // intermediate objects.
206  std::vector<UnorderedHeapObjectSet> indirect_strong_references_;
207 };
208 #endif

243 void HeapEntry::VerifyReference(HeapGraphEdge::Type type, HeapEntry* entry,
244  HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator,
245  ReferenceVerification verification) {
246 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_HEAP_SNAPSHOT_VERIFY
247  if (verification == kOffHeapPointer || generator->verifier() == nullptr) {
248  // Off-heap pointers are outside the scope of this verification; we just
249  // trust the embedder to provide accurate data. If the verifier is null,
250  // then verification is disabled.
251  return;
252  }
253  if (verification == kCustomWeakPointer) {
254  // The caller declared that this is a weak pointer ignored by the marking
255  // visitor. All we can verify at this point is that the edge type declares
256  // it to be weak.
257  CHECK_EQ(type, HeapGraphEdge::kWeak);
258  return;
259  }
260  Address from_address =
261  reinterpret_cast<Address>(generator->FindHeapThingForHeapEntry(this));
262  Address to_address =
263  reinterpret_cast<Address>(generator->FindHeapThingForHeapEntry(entry));
264  if (from_address == kNullAddress || to_address == kNullAddress) {
265  // One of these entries doesn't correspond to a real heap object.
266  // Verification is not possible.
267  return;
268  }
269  Tagged<HeapObject> from_obj = Cast<HeapObject>(Tagged<Object>(from_address));
270  Tagged<HeapObject> to_obj = Cast<HeapObject>(Tagged<Object>(to_address));
271  if (MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(to_obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
272  // We can't verify pointers into read-only space, because marking visitors
273  // might not mark those. For example, every Map has a pointer to the
274  // MetaMap, but marking visitors don't bother with following that link.
275  // Read-only objects are immortal and can never point to things outside of
276  // read-only space, so ignoring these objects is safe from the perspective
277  // of ensuring accurate retaining paths for normal read-write objects.
278  // Therefore, do nothing.
279  } else if (verification == kEphemeron) {
280  // Ephemerons can't be verified because they aren't marked directly by the
281  // marking visitor.
282  generator->verifier()->MarkReferenceCheckedWithoutChecking(from_obj,
283  to_obj);
284  } else if (type == HeapGraphEdge::kWeak) {
285  generator->verifier()->CheckWeakReference(from_obj, to_obj);
286  } else {
287  generator->verifier()->CheckStrongReference(from_obj, to_obj);
288  }
289 #endif
290 }

323 void HeapEntry::Print(const char* prefix, const char* edge_name, int max_depth,
324  int indent) const {
325  static_assert(sizeof(unsigned) == sizeof(id()));
326  base::OS::Print("%6zu @%6u %*c %s%s: ", self_size(), id(), indent, ' ',
327  prefix, edge_name);
328  if (type() != kString) {
329  base::OS::Print("%s %.40s\n", TypeAsString(), name_);
330  } else {
331  base::OS::Print("\"");
332  const char* c = name_;
333  while (*c && (c - name_) <= 40) {
334  if (*c != '\n')
335  base::OS::Print("%c", *c);
336  else
337  base::OS::Print("\\n");
338  ++c;
339  }
340  base::OS::Print("\"\n");
341  }
342  if (--max_depth == 0) return;
343  for (auto i = children_begin(); i != children_end(); ++i) {
344  HeapGraphEdge& edge = **i;
345  const char* edge_prefix = "";
346  base::EmbeddedVector<char, 64> index;
347  edge_name = index.begin();
348  switch (edge.type()) {
349  case HeapGraphEdge::kContextVariable:
350  edge_prefix = "#";
351  edge_name = edge.name();
352  break;
353  case HeapGraphEdge::kElement:
354  SNPrintF(index, "%d", edge.index());
355  break;
356  case HeapGraphEdge::kInternal:
357  edge_prefix = "$";
358  edge_name = edge.name();
359  break;
360  case HeapGraphEdge::kProperty:
361  edge_name = edge.name();
362  break;
363  case HeapGraphEdge::kHidden:
364  edge_prefix = "$";
365  SNPrintF(index, "%d", edge.index());
366  break;
367  case HeapGraphEdge::kShortcut:
368  edge_prefix = "^";
369  edge_name = edge.name();
370  break;
371  case HeapGraphEdge::kWeak:
372  edge_prefix = "w";
373  edge_name = edge.name();
374  break;
375  default:
376  SNPrintF(index, "!!! unknown edge type: %d ", edge.type());
377  }
378  edge.to()->Print(edge_prefix, edge_name, max_depth, indent + 2);
379  }
380 }

382 const char* HeapEntry::TypeAsString() const {
383  switch (type()) {
384  case kHidden:
385  return "/hidden/";
386  case kObject:
387  return "/object/";
388  case kClosure:
389  return "/closure/";
390  case kString:
391  return "/string/";
392  case kCode:
393  return "/code/";
394  case kArray:
395  return "/array/";
396  case kRegExp:
397  return "/regexp/";
398  case kHeapNumber:
399  return "/number/";
400  case kNative:
401  return "/native/";
402  case kSynthetic:
403  return "/synthetic/";
404  case kConsString:
405  return "/concatenated string/";
406  case kSlicedString:
407  return "/sliced string/";
408  case kSymbol:
409  return "/symbol/";
410  case kBigInt:
411  return "/bigint/";
412  case kObjectShape:
413  return "/object shape/";
414  default:
415  return "???";
416  }
417 }

419 HeapSnapshot::HeapSnapshot(HeapProfiler* profiler,
420  v8::HeapProfiler::HeapSnapshotMode snapshot_mode,
421  v8::HeapProfiler::NumericsMode numerics_mode)
422  : profiler_(profiler),
423  snapshot_mode_(snapshot_mode),
424  numerics_mode_(numerics_mode) {
425  // It is very important to keep objects that form a heap snapshot
426  // as small as possible. Check assumptions about data structure sizes.
427  static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 4 || sizeof(HeapGraphEdge) == 12);
428  static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 8 || sizeof(HeapGraphEdge) == 24);
429  static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 4 || sizeof(HeapEntry) == 32);
430 #if V8_CC_MSVC
431  static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 8 || sizeof(HeapEntry) == 48);
432 #else // !V8_CC_MSVC
433  static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 8 || sizeof(HeapEntry) == 40);
434 #endif // !V8_CC_MSVC
435  memset(&gc_subroot_entries_, 0, sizeof(gc_subroot_entries_));
436 }

444 void HeapSnapshot::AddSyntheticRootEntries() {
445  AddRootEntry();
446  AddGcRootsEntry();
447  SnapshotObjectId id = HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsFirstSubrootId;
448  for (int root = 0; root < static_cast<int>(Root::kNumberOfRoots); root++) {
449  AddGcSubrootEntry(static_cast<Root>(root), id);
450  id += HeapObjectsMap::kObjectIdStep;
451  }
452  DCHECK_EQ(HeapObjectsMap::kFirstAvailableObjectId, id);
453 }

455 void HeapSnapshot::AddRootEntry() {
456  DCHECK_NULL(root_entry_);
457  DCHECK(entries_.empty()); // Root entry must be the first one.
458  root_entry_ = AddEntry(HeapEntry::kSynthetic, "",
459  HeapObjectsMap::kInternalRootObjectId, 0, 0);
460  DCHECK_EQ(1u, entries_.size());
461  DCHECK_EQ(root_entry_, &entries_.front());
462 }

501 void HeapSnapshot::FillChildren() {
502  DCHECK(children().empty());
503  int children_index = 0;
504  for (HeapEntry& entry : entries()) {
505  children_index = entry.set_children_index(children_index);
506  }
507  DCHECK_EQ(edges().size(), static_cast<size_t>(children_index));
508  children().resize(edges().size());
509  for (HeapGraphEdge& edge : edges()) {
510  edge.from()->add_child(&edge);
511  }
512 }

514 HeapEntry* HeapSnapshot::GetEntryById(SnapshotObjectId id) {
515  if (entries_by_id_cache_.empty()) {
516  CHECK(is_complete());
517  entries_by_id_cache_.reserve(entries_.size());
518  for (HeapEntry& entry : entries_) {
519  entries_by_id_cache_.emplace(entry.id(), &entry);
520  }
521  }
522  auto it = entries_by_id_cache_.find(id);
523  return it != entries_by_id_cache_.end() ? it->second : nullptr;
524 }

528 // We split IDs on evens for embedder objects (see
529 // HeapObjectsMap::GenerateId) and odds for native objects.
530 const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kInternalRootObjectId = 1;
531 const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsObjectId =
532  HeapObjectsMap::kInternalRootObjectId + HeapObjectsMap::kObjectIdStep;
533 const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsFirstSubrootId =
534  HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsObjectId + HeapObjectsMap::kObjectIdStep;
535 const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kFirstAvailableObjectId =
536  HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsFirstSubrootId +
537  static_cast<int>(Root::kNumberOfRoots) * HeapObjectsMap::kObjectIdStep;
538 const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kFirstAvailableNativeId = 2;

542 const v8::String::ExternalStringResourceBase* GetExternalStringResource(
543  Tagged<ExternalString> object, PtrComprCageBase cage_base) {
544  if (IsExternalOneByteString(object, cage_base)) {

550 int ExternalStringSizeForSnapshot(Tagged<ExternalString> object,
551  PtrComprCageBase cage_base) {
552  const v8::String::ExternalStringResourceBase* resource =
553  GetExternalStringResource(object, cage_base);
554  size_t external_string_size = resource ? resource->EstimateMemoryUsage() : 0;
555  if (external_string_size ==
556  v8::String::ExternalStringResourceBase::kDefaultMemoryEstimate) {
557  return object->ExternalPayloadSize();
558  }
559  DCHECK_LE(external_string_size, std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
560  return base::saturated_cast<int>(external_string_size);
561 }

563 int SizeForSnapshot(Tagged<HeapObject> object, PtrComprCageBase cage_base) {
564  // Since read-only space can be shared among Isolates, and JS developers have
565  // no control over the size of read-only space, we represent read-only objects
566  // as having zero size.
567  if (HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(object)) return 0;
568  int size = object->Size(cage_base);
569  if (IsExternalString(object, cage_base)) {
570  size +=
571  ExternalStringSizeForSnapshot(Cast<ExternalString>(object), cage_base);
572  }
573  return size;
574 }

578 HeapObjectsMap::HeapObjectsMap(Heap* heap)
579  : next_id_(kFirstAvailableObjectId),
580  next_native_id_(kFirstAvailableNativeId),
581  heap_(heap) {
582  // The dummy element at zero index is needed as entries_map_ cannot hold
583  // an entry with zero value. Otherwise it's impossible to tell if
584  // LookupOrInsert has added a new item or just returning exisiting one
585  // having the value of zero.
586  entries_.emplace_back(0, kNullAddress, 0, true);
587 }

589 bool HeapObjectsMap::MoveObject(Address from, Address to, int object_size) {
590  DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, to);
591  DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, from);
592  if (from == to) return false;
593  void* from_value = entries_map_.Remove(reinterpret_cast<void*>(from),
594  ComputeAddressHash(from));
595  if (from_value == nullptr) {
596  // It may occur that some untracked object moves to an address X and there
597  // is a tracked object at that address. In this case we should remove the
598  // entry as we know that the object has died.
599  void* to_value = entries_map_.Remove(reinterpret_cast<void*>(to),
600  ComputeAddressHash(to));
601  if (to_value != nullptr) {
602  int to_entry_info_index =
603  static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to_value));
604  entries_.at(to_entry_info_index).addr = kNullAddress;
605  }
606  } else {
607  base::HashMap::Entry* to_entry = entries_map_.LookupOrInsert(
608  reinterpret_cast<void*>(to), ComputeAddressHash(to));
609  if (to_entry->value != nullptr) {
610  // We found the existing entry with to address for an old object.
611  // Without this operation we will have two EntryInfo's with the same
612  // value in addr field. It is bad because later at RemoveDeadEntries
613  // one of this entry will be removed with the corresponding entries_map_
614  // entry.
615  int to_entry_info_index =
616  static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to_entry->value));
617  entries_.at(to_entry_info_index).addr = kNullAddress;
618  }
619  int from_entry_info_index =
620  static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(from_value));
621  entries_.at(from_entry_info_index).addr = to;
622  // Size of an object can change during its life, so to keep information
623  // about the object in entries_ consistent, we have to adjust size when the
624  // object is migrated.
625  if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
626  PrintF("Move object from %p to %p old size %6d new size %6d\n",
627  reinterpret_cast<void*>(from), reinterpret_cast<void*>(to),
628  entries_.at(from_entry_info_index).size, object_size);
629  }
630  entries_.at(from_entry_info_index).size = object_size;
631  to_entry->value = from_value;
632  }
633  return from_value != nullptr;
634 }

636 void HeapObjectsMap::UpdateObjectSize(Address addr, int size) {
637  FindOrAddEntry(addr, size, MarkEntryAccessed::kNo);
638 }
639 
640 SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::FindEntry(Address addr) {
641  base::HashMap::Entry* entry = entries_map_.Lookup(
642  reinterpret_cast<void*>(addr), ComputeAddressHash(addr));
643  if (entry == nullptr) return v8::HeapProfiler::kUnknownObjectId;
644  int entry_index = static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(entry->value));
645  EntryInfo& entry_info = entries_.at(entry_index);
646  DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(entries_.size()) > entries_map_.occupancy());
647  return entry_info.id;
648 }
649 
650 SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::FindOrAddEntry(
651  Address addr, unsigned int size, MarkEntryAccessed accessed,
652  IsNativeObject is_native_object) {
653  bool accessed_bool = accessed == MarkEntryAccessed::kYes;
654  bool is_native_object_bool = is_native_object == IsNativeObject::kYes;
655  DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(entries_.size()) > entries_map_.occupancy());
656  base::HashMap::Entry* entry = entries_map_.LookupOrInsert(
657  reinterpret_cast<void*>(addr), ComputeAddressHash(addr));
658  if (entry->value != nullptr) {
659  int entry_index =
660  static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(entry->value));
661  EntryInfo& entry_info = entries_.at(entry_index);
662  entry_info.accessed = accessed_bool;
663  if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
664  PrintF("Update object size : %p with old size %d and new size %d\n",
665  reinterpret_cast<void*>(addr), entry_info.size, size);
666  }
667  entry_info.size = size;
668  DCHECK_EQ(is_native_object_bool, entry_info.id % 2 == 0);
669  return entry_info.id;
670  }
671  entry->value = reinterpret_cast<void*>(entries_.size());
672  SnapshotObjectId id =
673  is_native_object_bool ? get_next_native_id() : get_next_id();
674  entries_.push_back(EntryInfo(id, addr, size, accessed_bool));
675  DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(entries_.size()) > entries_map_.occupancy());
676  return id;
677 }

679 SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::FindMergedNativeEntry(NativeObject addr) {
680  auto it = merged_native_entries_map_.find(addr);
681  if (it == merged_native_entries_map_.end())
682  return v8::HeapProfiler::kUnknownObjectId;
683  return entries_[it->second].id;
684 }

686 void HeapObjectsMap::AddMergedNativeEntry(NativeObject addr,
687  Address canonical_addr) {
688  base::HashMap::Entry* entry =
689  entries_map_.Lookup(reinterpret_cast<void*>(canonical_addr),
690  ComputeAddressHash(canonical_addr));
691  auto result = merged_native_entries_map_.insert(
692  {addr, reinterpret_cast<size_t>(entry->value)});
693  if (!result.second) {
694  result.first->second = reinterpret_cast<size_t>(entry->value);
695  }
696 }

700 void HeapObjectsMap::UpdateHeapObjectsMap() {
701  if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
702  PrintF("Begin HeapObjectsMap::UpdateHeapObjectsMap. map has %d entries.\n",
703  entries_map_.occupancy());
704  }
705  heap_->PreciseCollectAllGarbage(GCFlag::kNoFlags,
706  GarbageCollectionReason::kHeapProfiler);
707  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(heap_->isolate());
708  CombinedHeapObjectIterator iterator(heap_);
709  for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj = iterator.Next(); !obj.is_null();
710  obj = iterator.Next()) {
711  FindOrAddEntry(obj.address(), SizeForSnapshot(obj, cage_base));
712  if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
713  int object_size = obj->Size(cage_base);
714  PrintF("Update object : %p %6d. Next address is %p\n",
715  reinterpret_cast<void*>(obj.address()), object_size,
716  reinterpret_cast<void*>(obj.address() + object_size));
717  }
718  }
719  RemoveDeadEntries();
720  if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
721  PrintF("End HeapObjectsMap::UpdateHeapObjectsMap. map has %d entries.\n",
722  entries_map_.occupancy());
723  }
724 }

726 SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::PushHeapObjectsStats(OutputStream* stream,
727  int64_t* timestamp_us) {
728  UpdateHeapObjectsMap();
729  time_intervals_.emplace_back(next_id_);
730  int prefered_chunk_size = stream->GetChunkSize();
731  std::vector<v8::HeapStatsUpdate> stats_buffer;
732  DCHECK(!entries_.empty());
733  EntryInfo* entry_info = &entries_.front();
734  EntryInfo* end_entry_info = &entries_.back() + 1;
735  for (size_t time_interval_index = 0;
736  time_interval_index < time_intervals_.size(); ++time_interval_index) {
737  TimeInterval& time_interval = time_intervals_[time_interval_index];
738  SnapshotObjectId time_interval_id = time_interval.id;
739  uint32_t entries_size = 0;
740  EntryInfo* start_entry_info = entry_info;
741  while (entry_info < end_entry_info && entry_info->id < time_interval_id) {
742  entries_size += entry_info->size;
743  ++entry_info;
744  }
745  uint32_t entries_count =
746  static_cast<uint32_t>(entry_info - start_entry_info);
747  if (time_interval.count != entries_count ||
748  time_interval.size != entries_size) {
749  stats_buffer.emplace_back(static_cast<uint32_t>(time_interval_index),
750  time_interval.count = entries_count,
751  time_interval.size = entries_size);
752  if (static_cast<int>(stats_buffer.size()) >= prefered_chunk_size) {
753  OutputStream::WriteResult result = stream->WriteHeapStatsChunk(
754  &stats_buffer.front(), static_cast<int>(stats_buffer.size()));
755  if (result == OutputStream::kAbort) return last_assigned_id();
756  stats_buffer.clear();
757  }
758  }
759  }
760  DCHECK(entry_info == end_entry_info);
761  if (!stats_buffer.empty()) {
762  OutputStream::WriteResult result = stream->WriteHeapStatsChunk(
763  &stats_buffer.front(), static_cast<int>(stats_buffer.size()));
764  if (result == OutputStream::kAbort) return last_assigned_id();
765  }
766  stream->EndOfStream();
767  if (timestamp_us) {
768  *timestamp_us =
769  (time_intervals_.back().timestamp - time_intervals_.front().timestamp)
770  .InMicroseconds();
771  }
772  return last_assigned_id();
773 }
774 
775 void HeapObjectsMap::RemoveDeadEntries() {
776  DCHECK(entries_.size() > 0 && entries_.at(0).id == 0 &&
777  entries_.at(0).addr == kNullAddress);
778 
779  // Build up temporary reverse map.
780  std::unordered_map<size_t, NativeObject> reverse_merged_native_entries_map;
781  for (const auto& it : merged_native_entries_map_) {
782  auto result =
783  reverse_merged_native_entries_map.emplace(it.second, it.first);
784  DCHECK(result.second);
785  USE(result);
786  }
787 
788  size_t first_free_entry = 1;
789  for (size_t i = 1; i < entries_.size(); ++i) {
790  EntryInfo& entry_info = entries_.at(i);
791  auto merged_reverse_it = reverse_merged_native_entries_map.find(i);
792  if (entry_info.accessed) {
793  if (first_free_entry != i) {
794  entries_.at(first_free_entry) = entry_info;
795  }
796  entries_.at(first_free_entry).accessed = false;
797  base::HashMap::Entry* entry =
798  entries_map_.Lookup(reinterpret_cast<void*>(entry_info.addr),
799  ComputeAddressHash(entry_info.addr));
800  DCHECK(entry);
801  entry->value = reinterpret_cast<void*>(first_free_entry);
802  if (merged_reverse_it != reverse_merged_native_entries_map.end()) {
803  auto it = merged_native_entries_map_.find(merged_reverse_it->second);
804  DCHECK_NE(merged_native_entries_map_.end(), it);
805  it->second = first_free_entry;
806  }
807  ++first_free_entry;
808  } else {
809  if (entry_info.addr) {
810  entries_map_.Remove(reinterpret_cast<void*>(entry_info.addr),
811  ComputeAddressHash(entry_info.addr));
812  if (merged_reverse_it != reverse_merged_native_entries_map.end()) {
813  merged_native_entries_map_.erase(merged_reverse_it->second);
814  }
815  }
816  }
817  }
818  entries_.erase(entries_.begin() + first_free_entry, entries_.end());
819 
820  DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(entries_.size()) - 1 ==
821  entries_map_.occupancy());
822 }

895 HeapEntry* V8HeapExplorer::AddEntry(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
896  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate());
897  InstanceType instance_type = object->map(cage_base)->instance_type();
898  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(instance_type)) {
899  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(instance_type)) {
900  Tagged<JSFunction> func = Cast<JSFunction>(object);
901  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = func->shared();
902  const char* name = names_->GetName(shared->Name());
903  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kClosure, name);
904 
905  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSBoundFunction(instance_type)) {
906  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kClosure, "native_bind");
907  }
908  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSRegExp(instance_type)) {
909  Tagged<JSRegExp> re = Cast<JSRegExp>(object);
910  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kRegExp,
911  names_->GetName(re->source()));
912  }
913  // TODO(v8:12674) Fix and run full gcmole.
914  DisableGCMole no_gcmole;
915  const char* name = names_->GetName(
916  GetConstructorName(heap_->isolate(), Cast<JSObject>(object)));
917  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSGlobalObject(instance_type)) {
918  auto it = global_object_tag_map_.find(Cast<JSGlobalObject>(object));
919  if (it != global_object_tag_map_.end()) {
920  name = names_->GetFormatted("%s / %s", name, it->second);
921  }
922  }
923  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kObject, name);
924 
925  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(instance_type)) {
926  Tagged<String> string = Cast<String>(object);
927  if (IsConsString(string, cage_base)) {
928  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kConsString, "(concatenated string)");
929  } else if (IsSlicedString(string, cage_base)) {
930  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kSlicedString, "(sliced string)");
931  } else {
932  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kString,
933  names_->GetName(Cast<String>(object)));
934  }
935  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsSymbol(instance_type)) {
936  if (Cast<Symbol>(object)->is_private())
937  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kHidden, "private symbol");
938  else
939  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kSymbol, "symbol");
940 
941  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsBigInt(instance_type)) {
942  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kBigInt, "bigint");
943 
944  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsInstructionStream(instance_type) ||
945  InstanceTypeChecker::IsCode(instance_type)) {
946  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kCode, "");
947 
948  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsSharedFunctionInfo(instance_type)) {
949  Tagged<String> name = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(object)->Name();
950  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kCode, names_->GetName(name));
951 
952  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsScript(instance_type)) {
953  Tagged<Object> name = Cast<Script>(object)->name();
954  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kCode,
955  IsString(name) ? names_->GetName(Cast<String>(name)) : "");
956 
957  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsNativeContext(instance_type)) {
958  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kHidden, "system / NativeContext");
959 
960  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsContext(instance_type)) {
961  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kObject, "system / Context");
962 
963  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsHeapNumber(instance_type)) {
964  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kHeapNumber, "heap number");
965  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsOddball(instance_type)) {
966  Tagged<String> name = Cast<Oddball>(object)->to_string();
967  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kHidden, names_->GetName(name));
968  } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsCppHeapExternalObject(instance_type)) {
969  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kObject, "system / CppHeapExternal");
970  }
971 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
972  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsWasmObject(instance_type)) {
973  Tagged<WasmTypeInfo> info = object->map()->wasm_type_info();
974  wasm::StringBuilder sb;
975  wasm::GetCanonicalTypeNamesProvider()->PrintTypeName(sb,
976  info->type_index());
977  sb << " (wasm)" << '\0';
978  const char* name = names_->GetCopy(sb.start());
979  return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kObject, name);
980  }
981 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
982 
983  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsForeign(instance_type)) {
984  Tagged<Foreign> foreign = Cast<Foreign>(object);
985  ExternalPointerTag tag = foreign->GetTag();
986 
987  size_t size = SizeForSnapshot(object, cage_base);
988  const char* name = nullptr;
989  // TODO(saelo): consider creating a global mapping of ExternalPointerTags
990  // for Managed objects to their name if we need this anywhere else.
991  switch (tag) {
992  case kGenericManagedTag:
993  name = "system / Managed<Unknown>";
994  break;
995 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
996  case kWasmWasmStreamingTag:
997  name = "system / Managed<WasmStreaming>";
998  break;
999  case kWasmFuncDataTag:
1000  name = "system / Managed<wasm::FuncData>";
1001  break;
1002  case kWasmManagedDataTag:
1003  name = "system / Managed<wasm::ManagedData>";
1004  break;
1005  case kWasmNativeModuleTag:
1006  size = Cast<Managed<wasm::NativeModule>>(foreign)
1007  ->raw()
1008  ->EstimateCurrentMemoryConsumption();
1009  name = "system / Managed<wasm::NativeModule>";
1010  break;
1011 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1012  case kIcuBreakIteratorTag:
1013  name = "system / Managed<icu::BreakIterator>";
1014  break;
1015  case kIcuUnicodeStringTag:
1016  name = "system / Managed<icu::UnicodeString>";
1017  break;
1018  case kIcuListFormatterTag:
1019  name = "system / Managed<icu::ListFormatter>";
1020  break;
1021  case kIcuLocaleTag:
1022  name = "system / Managed<icu::Locale>";
1023  break;
1024  case kIcuSimpleDateFormatTag:
1025  name = "system / Managed<icu::SimpleDateFormat>";
1026  break;
1027  case kIcuDateIntervalFormatTag:
1028  name = "system / Managed<icu::DateIntervalFormat>";
1029  break;
1030  case kIcuRelativeDateTimeFormatterTag:
1031  name = "system / Managed<icu::RelativeDateTimeFormatter>";
1032  break;
1033  case kIcuLocalizedNumberFormatterTag:
1034  name = "system / Managed<icu::LocalizedNumberFormatter>";
1035  break;
1036  case kIcuPluralRulesTag:
1037  name = "system / Managed<icu::PluralRules>";
1038  break;
1039  case kIcuCollatorTag:
1040  name = "system / Managed<icu::Collator>";
1041  break;
1042  case kDisplayNamesInternalTag:
1043  name = "system / Managed<DisplayNamesInternal>";
1044  break;
1045  case kTemporalInstantTag:
1046  name = "system / Managed<temporal_rs::Instant>";
1047  break;
1048  case kD8WorkerTag:
1049  name = "system / Managed<d8::Worker>";
1050  break;
1051  case kD8ModuleEmbedderDataTag:
1052  name = "system / Managed<d8::ModuleEmbedderData>";
1053  break;
1054  default:
1055  DCHECK(!kAnyManagedExternalPointerTagRange.Contains(tag));
1056  }
1057  if (name != nullptr) {
1058  return AddEntry(object.address(), HeapEntry::kHidden, name, size);
1059  }
1060  }
1061 
1062  return AddEntry(object, GetSystemEntryType(object),
1063  GetSystemEntryName(object));
1064 }

1073 HeapEntry* V8HeapExplorer::AddEntry(Address address, HeapEntry::Type type,
1074  const char* name, size_t size) {
1075  if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_show_hidden_objects &&
1076  type == HeapEntry::kHidden) {
1077  type = HeapEntry::kNative;
1078  }
1079  SnapshotObjectId object_id = heap_object_map_->FindOrAddEntry(
1080  address, static_cast<unsigned int>(size));
1081  unsigned trace_node_id = 0;
1082  if (AllocationTracker* allocation_tracker =
1083  snapshot_->profiler()->allocation_tracker()) {
1084  trace_node_id =
1085  allocation_tracker->address_to_trace()->GetTraceNodeId(address);
1086  }
1087  return snapshot_->AddEntry(type, name, object_id, size, trace_node_id);
1088 }

1090 const char* V8HeapExplorer::GetSystemEntryName(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
1091  if (IsMap(object)) {
1092  switch (Cast<Map>(object)->instance_type()) {
1093 #define MAKE_STRING_MAP_CASE(instance_type, size, name, Name) \
1094  case instance_type: \
1095  return "system / Map (" #Name ")";
1096  STRING_TYPE_LIST(MAKE_STRING_MAP_CASE)
1097 #undef MAKE_STRING_MAP_CASE
1098  default:
1099  return "system / Map";
1100  }
1101  }
1102 
1103  InstanceType type = object->map()->instance_type();
1104 
1105  // Empty string names are special: TagObject can overwrite them, and devtools
1106  // will report them as "(internal array)".
1107  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsFixedArray(type) ||
1108  InstanceTypeChecker::IsFixedDoubleArray(type) ||
1109  InstanceTypeChecker::IsByteArray(type)) {
1110  return "";
1111  }
1112 
1113  switch (type) {
1114 #define MAKE_TORQUE_CASE(Name, TYPE) \
1115  case TYPE: \
1116  return "system / " #Name;
1117  // The following lists include every non-String instance type.
1118  // This includes a few types that already have non-"system" names assigned
1119  // by AddEntry, but this is a convenient way to avoid manual upkeep here.
1120  TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_SINGLE_FULLY_DEFINED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
1121  TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_MULTIPLE_FULLY_DEFINED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
1122  TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_SINGLE_ONLY_DECLARED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
1123  TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_MULTIPLE_ONLY_DECLARED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
1124 #undef MAKE_TORQUE_CASE
1125 
1126  // Strings were already handled by AddEntry.
1127 #define MAKE_STRING_CASE(instance_type, size, name, Name) \
1128  case instance_type: \
1129  UNREACHABLE();
1130  STRING_TYPE_LIST(MAKE_STRING_CASE)
1131 #undef MAKE_STRING_CASE
1132  }
1133 }
1134 
1135 HeapEntry::Type V8HeapExplorer::GetSystemEntryType(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
1136  InstanceType type = object->map()->instance_type();
1137  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsAllocationSite(type) ||
1138  InstanceTypeChecker::IsArrayBoilerplateDescription(type) ||
1139  InstanceTypeChecker::IsBytecodeArray(type) ||
1140  InstanceTypeChecker::IsBytecodeWrapper(type) ||
1141  InstanceTypeChecker::IsClosureFeedbackCellArray(type) ||
1142  InstanceTypeChecker::IsCode(type) ||
1143  InstanceTypeChecker::IsCodeWrapper(type) ||
1144  InstanceTypeChecker::IsFeedbackCell(type) ||
1145  InstanceTypeChecker::IsFeedbackMetadata(type) ||
1146  InstanceTypeChecker::IsFeedbackVector(type) ||
1147  InstanceTypeChecker::IsInstructionStream(type) ||
1148  InstanceTypeChecker::IsInterpreterData(type) ||
1149  InstanceTypeChecker::IsLoadHandler(type) ||
1150  InstanceTypeChecker::IsObjectBoilerplateDescription(type) ||
1151  InstanceTypeChecker::IsPreparseData(type) ||
1152  InstanceTypeChecker::IsRegExpBoilerplateDescription(type) ||
1153  InstanceTypeChecker::IsScopeInfo(type) ||
1154  InstanceTypeChecker::IsStoreHandler(type) ||
1155  InstanceTypeChecker::IsTemplateObjectDescription(type) ||
1156  InstanceTypeChecker::IsTurbofanType(type) ||
1157  InstanceTypeChecker::IsUncompiledData(type)) {
1158  return HeapEntry::kCode;
1159  }
1160 
1161  // This check must come second, because some subtypes of FixedArray are
1162  // determined above to represent code content.
1163  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsFixedArray(type) ||
1164  InstanceTypeChecker::IsFixedDoubleArray(type) ||
1165  InstanceTypeChecker::IsByteArray(type)) {
1166  return HeapEntry::kArray;
1167  }
1168 
1169  // Maps in read-only space are for internal V8 data, not user-defined object
1170  // shapes.
1171  if ((InstanceTypeChecker::IsMap(type) &&
1172  !MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(object)->InReadOnlySpace()) ||
1173  InstanceTypeChecker::IsDescriptorArray(type) ||
1174  InstanceTypeChecker::IsTransitionArray(type) ||
1175  InstanceTypeChecker::IsPrototypeInfo(type) ||
1176  InstanceTypeChecker::IsEnumCache(type)) {
1177  return HeapEntry::kObjectShape;
1178  }
1179 
1180  return HeapEntry::kHidden;
1181 }

1183 void V8HeapExplorer::PopulateLineEnds() {
1184  std::vector<Handle<Script>> scripts;
1185  HandleScope scope(isolate());
1186 
1187  {
1188  Script::Iterator iterator(isolate());
1189  for (Tagged<Script> script = iterator.Next(); !script.is_null();
1190  script = iterator.Next()) {
1191  if (!script->has_line_ends()) {
1192  scripts.push_back(handle(script, isolate()));
1193  }
1194  }
1195  }
1196 
1197  for (auto& script : scripts) {
1198  snapshot_->AddScriptLineEnds(script->id(),
1199  Script::GetLineEnds(isolate(), script));
1200  }
1201 }

1203 uint32_t V8HeapExplorer::EstimateObjectsCount() {
1204  CombinedHeapObjectIterator it(heap_, HeapObjectIterator::kNoFiltering);
1205  uint32_t objects_count = 0;
1206  // Avoid overflowing the objects count. In worst case, we will show the same
1207  // progress for a longer period of time, but we do not expect to have that
1208  // many objects.
1209  while (!it.Next().is_null() &&
1210  objects_count != std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max())
1211  ++objects_count;
1212  return objects_count;
1213 }

1215 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
1216 namespace {
1217 int AdjustEmbedderFieldIndex(Tagged<HeapObject> heap_obj, int field_index) {
1218  Tagged<Map> map = heap_obj->map();
1219  if (JSObject::MayHaveEmbedderFields(map)) {
1220  int emb_start_index = (JSObject::GetEmbedderFieldsStartOffset(map) +
1221  EmbedderDataSlot::kTaggedPayloadOffset) /
1222  kTaggedSize;
1223  int emb_field_count = JSObject::GetEmbedderFieldCount(map);
1224  int emb_end_index = emb_start_index + emb_field_count;
1225  if (base::IsInRange(field_index, emb_start_index, emb_end_index)) {
1226  return -EmbedderDataSlot::kTaggedPayloadOffset / kTaggedSize;
1227  }
1228  }
1229  return 0;
1230 }
1231 } // namespace

1236  Tagged<HeapObject> parent_obj, HeapEntry* parent)
1237  : ObjectVisitorWithCageBases(generator->isolate()),
1238  generator_(generator),
1239  parent_obj_(parent_obj),

1241  parent_end_(
1242  parent_obj_->RawMaybeWeakField(parent_obj_->Size(cage_base()))),

1246  ObjectSlot end) override {
1247  VisitPointers(host, MaybeObjectSlot(start), MaybeObjectSlot(end));

1250  VisitSlotImpl(cage_base(), object->map_slot());
1251  }
1252  void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, MaybeObjectSlot start,
1253  MaybeObjectSlot end) override {
1254  // [start,end) must be a sub-region of [parent_start_, parent_end), i.e.
1255  // all the slots must point inside the object.
1256  CHECK_LE(parent_start_, start);
1257  CHECK_LE(end, parent_end_);
1258  for (MaybeObjectSlot slot = start; slot < end; ++slot) {
1259  VisitSlotImpl(cage_base(), slot);
1260  }

1309  void VisitJSDispatchTableEntry(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
1310  JSDispatchHandle handle) override {
1311 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1312  // TODO(saelo): implement proper support for these fields here, similar to
1313  // how we handle indirect pointer or protected pointer fields.
1314  // Currently we only expect to see FeedbackCells or JSFunctions here.
1315  if (IsJSFunction(host)) {
1316  int field_index = JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset / kTaggedSize;
1317  CHECK(generator_->visited_fields_[field_index]);
1318  generator_->visited_fields_[field_index] = false;
1319  } else if (IsCode(host) || IsFeedbackCell(host)) {
1320  // Nothing to do: the Code object is tracked as part of the JSFunction.
1321  } else {
1322  UNREACHABLE();
1323  }
1324 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1325  }
1326 
1327  private:
1328  template <typename TIsolateOrCageBase, typename TSlot>
1329  V8_INLINE void VisitSlotImpl(TIsolateOrCageBase isolate_or_cage_base,
1330  TSlot slot) {
1331  int field_index =
1332  static_cast<int>(slot.address() - parent_start_.address()) /
1333  TSlot::kSlotDataSize;
1334 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
1335  field_index += AdjustEmbedderFieldIndex(parent_obj_, field_index);
1336 #endif
1337  DCHECK_GE(field_index, 0);
1338  if (generator_->visited_fields_[field_index]) {
1339  generator_->visited_fields_[field_index] = false;
1340  } else {
1341  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
1342  auto loaded_value = slot.load(isolate_or_cage_base);
1343  if (loaded_value.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&heap_object)) {
1344  VisitHeapObjectImpl(heap_object, field_index);
1345  } else if (loaded_value.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&heap_object)) {
1346  generator_->SetWeakReference(parent_, next_index_++, heap_object, {});
1347  }
1348  }
1349  }
1350 
1351  V8_INLINE void VisitHeapObjectImpl(Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object,
1352  int field_index) {
1353  DCHECK_LE(-1, field_index);
1354  // The last parameter {field_offset} is only used to check some well-known
1355  // skipped references, so passing -1 * kTaggedSize for objects embedded
1356  // into code is fine.
1357  generator_->SetHiddenReference(parent_obj_, parent_, next_index_++,
1358  heap_object, field_index * kTaggedSize);
1359  }
1360 
1361  V8HeapExplorer* generator_;
1362  Tagged<HeapObject> parent_obj_;
1363  MaybeObjectSlot parent_start_;
1364  MaybeObjectSlot parent_end_;
1365  HeapEntry* parent_;
1366  int next_index_;
1367 };

1482 void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractJSObjectReferences(HeapEntry* entry,
1483  Tagged<JSObject> js_obj) {
1484  Tagged<HeapObject> obj = js_obj;
1485  ExtractPropertyReferences(js_obj, entry);
1486  ExtractElementReferences(js_obj, entry);
1487  ExtractInternalReferences(js_obj, entry);
1488  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::FromHeap(heap_);
1489  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, js_obj);
1490  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
1491  SetPropertyReference(entry, roots.proto_string(), iter.GetCurrent());
1492  if (IsJSBoundFunction(obj)) {
1493  Tagged<JSBoundFunction> js_fun = Cast<JSBoundFunction>(obj);
1494  TagObject(js_fun->bound_arguments(), "(bound arguments)");
1495  SetInternalReference(entry, "bindings", js_fun->bound_arguments(),
1496  JSBoundFunction::kBoundArgumentsOffset);
1497  SetInternalReference(entry, "bound_this", js_fun->bound_this(),
1498  JSBoundFunction::kBoundThisOffset);
1499  SetInternalReference(entry, "bound_function",
1500  js_fun->bound_target_function(),
1501  JSBoundFunction::kBoundTargetFunctionOffset);
1502  Tagged<FixedArray> bindings = js_fun->bound_arguments();
1503  for (int i = 0; i < bindings->length(); i++) {
1504  const char* reference_name = names_->GetFormatted("bound_argument_%d", i);
1505  SetNativeBindReference(entry, reference_name, bindings->get(i));
1506  }
1507  } else if (IsJSFunction(obj)) {
1508  Tagged<JSFunction> js_fun = Cast<JSFunction>(js_obj);
1509  if (js_fun->has_prototype_slot()) {
1510  Tagged<Object> proto_or_map =
1511  js_fun->prototype_or_initial_map(kAcquireLoad);
1512  if (!IsTheHole(proto_or_map, isolate)) {
1513  if (!IsMap(proto_or_map)) {
1514  SetPropertyReference(entry, roots.prototype_string(), proto_or_map,
1515  nullptr,
1516  JSFunction::kPrototypeOrInitialMapOffset);
1517  } else {
1518  SetPropertyReference(entry, roots.prototype_string(),
1519  js_fun->prototype());
1520  SetInternalReference(entry, "initial_map", proto_or_map,
1521  JSFunction::kPrototypeOrInitialMapOffset);
1522  }
1523  }
1524  }
1525  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = js_fun->shared();
1526  TagObject(js_fun->raw_feedback_cell(), "(function feedback cell)");
1527  SetInternalReference(entry, "feedback_cell", js_fun->raw_feedback_cell(),
1528  JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset);
1529  TagObject(shared_info, "(shared function info)");
1530  SetInternalReference(entry, "shared", shared_info,
1531  JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset);
1532  TagObject(js_fun->context(), "(context)");
1533  SetInternalReference(entry, "context", js_fun->context(),
1534  JSFunction::kContextOffset);
1535 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1536  SetInternalReference(entry, "code", js_fun->code(isolate),
1537  JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset);
1538 #else
1539  SetInternalReference(entry, "code", js_fun->code(isolate),
1540  JSFunction::kCodeOffset);
1541 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1542  } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(obj)) {
1543  Tagged<JSGlobalObject> global_obj = Cast<JSGlobalObject>(obj);
1544  SetInternalReference(entry, "global_proxy", global_obj->global_proxy(),
1545  JSGlobalObject::kGlobalProxyOffset);
1546  } else if (IsJSArrayBufferView(obj)) {
1547  Tagged<JSArrayBufferView> view = Cast<JSArrayBufferView>(obj);
1548  SetInternalReference(entry, "buffer", view->buffer(),
1549  JSArrayBufferView::kBufferOffset);
1550  }
1551 
1552  TagObject(js_obj->raw_properties_or_hash(), "(object properties)");
1553  SetInternalReference(entry, "properties", js_obj->raw_properties_or_hash(),
1554  JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset);
1555 
1556  TagObject(js_obj->elements(), "(object elements)");
1557  SetInternalReference(entry, "elements", js_obj->elements(),
1558  JSObject::kElementsOffset);
1559 }

1653 void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractEphemeronHashTableReferences(

1657  EphemeronHashTable::kEntryKeyIndex;
1658  int value_index = EphemeronHashTable::EntryToValueIndex(i);
1659  Tagged<Object> key = table->get(key_index);
1660  Tagged<Object> value = table->get(value_index);
1661  SetWeakReference(entry, key_index, key,
1662  table->OffsetOfElementAt(key_index));
1663  SetWeakReference(entry, value_index, value,
1664  table->OffsetOfElementAt(value_index));
1665  HeapEntry* key_entry = GetEntry(key);
1666  HeapEntry* value_entry = GetEntry(value);
1667  HeapEntry* table_entry = GetEntry(table);
1668  if (key_entry && value_entry && !IsUndefined(key)) {
1669  const char* edge_name = names_->GetFormatted(
1670  "part of key (%s @%u) -> value (%s @%u) pair in WeakMap (table @%u)",
1671  key_entry->name(), key_entry->id(), value_entry->name(),
1672  value_entry->id(), table_entry->id());
1673  key_entry->SetNamedAutoIndexReference(HeapGraphEdge::kInternal, edge_name,
1674  value_entry, names_, generator_,
1675  HeapEntry::kEphemeron);
1676  table_entry->SetNamedAutoIndexReference(
1677  HeapGraphEdge::kInternal, edge_name, value_entry, names_, generator_,
1678  HeapEntry::kEphemeron);
1679  }
1680  }
1681 }

1694 // These static arrays are used to prevent excessive code-size in
1695 // ExtractContextReferences below, which would happen if we called
1696 // SetInternalReference for every native context field in a macro.
1697 static const struct {
1698  int index;
1699  const char* name;
1700 } native_context_names[] = {
1701 #define CONTEXT_FIELD_INDEX_NAME(index, _, name) {Context::index, #name},
1702  NATIVE_CONTEXT_FIELDS(CONTEXT_FIELD_INDEX_NAME)
1703 #undef CONTEXT_FIELD_INDEX_NAME
1704 };

1706 void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractContextReferences(HeapEntry* entry,
1707  Tagged<Context> context) {
1708  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1709  if (!IsNativeContext(context) && context->is_declaration_context()) {
1710  Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info = context->scope_info();
1711  // Add context allocated locals.
1712  for (auto it : ScopeInfo::IterateLocalNames(scope_info, no_gc)) {
1713  int idx = scope_info->ContextHeaderLength() + it->index();
1714  SetContextReference(entry, it->name(), context->get(idx, kRelaxedLoad),
1715  Context::OffsetOfElementAt(idx));
1716  }
1717  if (scope_info->HasContextAllocatedFunctionName()) {
1718  Tagged<String> name = Cast<String>(scope_info->FunctionName());
1719  int idx = scope_info->FunctionContextSlotIndex(name);
1720  if (idx >= 0) {
1721  SetContextReference(entry, name, context->get(idx, kRelaxedLoad),
1722  Context::OffsetOfElementAt(idx));
1723  }
1724  }
1725  }
1726 
1727  SetInternalReference(
1728  entry, "scope_info",
1729  context->get(Context::SCOPE_INFO_INDEX, kRelaxedLoad),
1730  FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::SCOPE_INFO_INDEX));
1731  SetInternalReference(entry, "previous",
1732  context->get(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX, kRelaxedLoad),
1733  FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
1734  if (context->has_extension()) {
1735  SetInternalReference(
1736  entry, "extension",
1737  context->get(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX, kRelaxedLoad),
1738  FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX));
1739  }
1740 
1741  if (IsNativeContext(context)) {
1742  TagObject(context->normalized_map_cache(), "(context norm. map cache)");
1743  TagObject(context->embedder_data(), "(context data)");
1744  for (size_t i = 0; i < arraysize(native_context_names); i++) {
1745  int index = native_context_names[i].index;
1746  const char* name = native_context_names[i].name;
1747  SetInternalReference(entry, name, context->get(index, kRelaxedLoad),
1748  FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(index));
1749  }
1750 
1751  static_assert(Context::NEXT_CONTEXT_LINK == Context::FIRST_WEAK_SLOT);
1752  static_assert(Context::FIRST_WEAK_SLOT + 1 ==
1753  Context::NATIVE_CONTEXT_SLOTS);
1754  }
1755 }

1757 void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractMapReferences(HeapEntry* entry, Tagged<Map> map) {
1758  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_raw_transitions_or_prototype_info =
1759  map->raw_transitions();
1760  Tagged<HeapObject> raw_transitions_or_prototype_info;
1761  if (maybe_raw_transitions_or_prototype_info.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(
1762  &raw_transitions_or_prototype_info)) {
1763  DCHECK(IsMap(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info));
1764  SetWeakReference(entry, "transition", raw_transitions_or_prototype_info,
1765  Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
1766  } else if (maybe_raw_transitions_or_prototype_info.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(
1767  &raw_transitions_or_prototype_info)) {
1768  if (IsTransitionArray(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info)) {
1769  Tagged<TransitionArray> transitions =
1770  Cast<TransitionArray>(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info);
1771  if (map->CanTransition() && transitions->HasPrototypeTransitions()) {
1772  TagObject(transitions->GetPrototypeTransitions(),
1773  "(prototype transitions)");
1774  }
1775  TagObject(transitions, "(transition array)");
1776  SetInternalReference(entry, "transitions", transitions,
1777  Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
1778  } else if (IsFixedArray(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info)) {
1779  TagObject(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info, "(transition)");
1780  SetInternalReference(entry, "transition",
1781  raw_transitions_or_prototype_info,
1782  Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
1783  } else if (map->is_prototype_map()) {
1784  TagObject(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info, "prototype_info");
1785  SetInternalReference(entry, "prototype_info",
1786  raw_transitions_or_prototype_info,
1787  Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
1788  }
1789  }
1790  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = map->instance_descriptors();
1791  TagObject(descriptors, "(map descriptors)");
1792  SetInternalReference(entry, "descriptors", descriptors,
1793  Map::kInstanceDescriptorsOffset);
1794  SetInternalReference(entry, "prototype", map->prototype(),
1795  Map::kPrototypeOffset);
1796  if (IsContextMap(map) || IsMapMap(map)) {
1797  Tagged<Object> native_context = map->native_context_or_null();
1798  TagObject(native_context, "(native context)");
1799  SetInternalReference(entry, "native_context", native_context,
1800  Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
1801  } else {
1802  Tagged<Object> constructor_or_back_pointer =
1803  map->constructor_or_back_pointer();
1804  if (IsMap(constructor_or_back_pointer)) {
1805  TagObject(constructor_or_back_pointer, "(back pointer)");
1806  SetInternalReference(entry, "back_pointer", constructor_or_back_pointer,
1807  Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
1808  } else if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(constructor_or_back_pointer)) {
1809  TagObject(constructor_or_back_pointer, "(constructor function data)");
1810  SetInternalReference(entry, "constructor_function_data",
1811  constructor_or_back_pointer,
1812  Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
1813  } else {
1814  SetInternalReference(entry, "constructor", constructor_or_back_pointer,
1815  Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
1816  }
1817  }
1818  TagObject(map->dependent_code(), "(dependent code)");
1819  SetInternalReference(entry, "dependent_code", map->dependent_code(),
1820  Map::kDependentCodeOffset);
1821  TagObject(map->prototype_validity_cell(kRelaxedLoad),
1822  "(prototype validity cell)", HeapEntry::kObjectShape);
1823 }

2080 void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractNumberReference(HeapEntry* entry,
2081  Tagged<Object> number) {

2083 
2084  // Must be large enough to fit any double, int, or size_t.
2085  char arr[32];
2086  base::Vector<char> buffer = base::ArrayVector(arr);
2087 
2088  std::string_view string;
2089  if (IsSmi(number)) {
2090  int int_value = Smi::ToInt(number);
2091  string = IntToStringView(int_value, buffer);

2096 
2097  // GetCopy() requires a null-terminated C-String, as the underlying hash map
2098  // uses strcmp.
2099  const char* name = names_->GetCopy(std::string(string).c_str());
2100 
2101  SnapshotObjectId id = heap_object_map_->get_next_id();
2102  HeapEntry* child_entry =
2103  snapshot_->AddEntry(HeapEntry::kString, name, id, 0, 0);
2104  entry->SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::kInternal, "value", child_entry,
2105  generator_);

2196 void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractPropertyReferences(Tagged<JSObject> js_obj,
2197  HeapEntry* entry) {
2198  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
2199  if (js_obj->HasFastProperties()) {
2200  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descs =
2201  js_obj->map()->instance_descriptors(isolate);
2202  for (InternalIndex i : js_obj->map()->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
2203  PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
2204  switch (details.location()) {
2205  case PropertyLocation::kField: {
2206  if (!snapshot_->capture_numeric_value()) {
2207  Representation r = details.representation();
2208  if (r.IsSmi() || r.IsDouble()) break;
2209  }
2210 
2211  Tagged<Name> k = descs->GetKey(i);
2212  FieldIndex field_index =
2213  FieldIndex::ForDetails(js_obj->map(), details);
2214  Tagged<Object> value = js_obj->RawFastPropertyAt(field_index);
2215  int field_offset =
2216  field_index.is_inobject() ? field_index.offset() : -1;
2217 
2218  SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry, k, value,
2219  nullptr, field_offset);
2220  break;
2221  }
2222  case PropertyLocation::kDescriptor:
2223  SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry,
2224  descs->GetKey(i),
2225  descs->GetStrongValue(i));
2226  break;
2227  }
2228  }
2229  } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(js_obj)) {
2230  // We assume that global objects can only have slow properties.
2231  Tagged<GlobalDictionary> dictionary =
2232  Cast<JSGlobalObject>(js_obj)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad);
2233  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2234  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
2235  if (!dictionary->IsKey(roots, dictionary->KeyAt(i))) continue;
2236  Tagged<PropertyCell> cell = dictionary->CellAt(i);
2237  Tagged<Name> name = cell->name();
2238  Tagged<Object> value = cell->value();
2239  PropertyDetails details = cell->property_details();
2240  SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry, name, value);
2241  }
2242  } else if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
2243  // SwissNameDictionary::IterateEntries creates a Handle, which should not
2244  // leak out of here.
2245  HandleScope scope(isolate);
2246 
2247  Tagged<SwissNameDictionary> dictionary =
2248  js_obj->property_dictionary_swiss();
2249  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2250  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
2251  Tagged<Object> k = dictionary->KeyAt(i);
2252  if (!dictionary->IsKey(roots, k)) continue;
2253  Tagged<Object> value = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
2254  PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(i);
2255  SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry, Cast<Name>(k),
2256  value);
2257  }
2258  } else {
2259  Tagged<NameDictionary> dictionary = js_obj->property_dictionary();
2260  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2261  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
2262  Tagged<Object> k = dictionary->KeyAt(i);
2263  if (!dictionary->IsKey(roots, k)) continue;
2264  Tagged<Object> value = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
2265  PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(i);
2266  SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry, Cast<Name>(k),
2267  value);
2268  }
2269  }

2329 void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractWasmStructReferences(Tagged<WasmStruct> obj,
2330  HeapEntry* entry) {
2331  Tagged<WasmTypeInfo> info = obj->map()->wasm_type_info();
2332  const wasm::CanonicalStructType* type =
2333  wasm::GetTypeCanonicalizer()->LookupStruct(info->type_index());
2334  wasm::CanonicalTypeNamesProvider* names =
2335  wasm::GetCanonicalTypeNamesProvider();
2336  Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
2337  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < type->field_count(); i++) {
2338  wasm::StringBuilder sb;
2339  names->PrintFieldName(sb, info->type_index(), i);
2340  sb << '\0';
2341  const char* field_name = names_->GetCopy(sb.start());
2342  switch (type->field(i).kind()) {
2343  case wasm::kI8:
2344  case wasm::kI16:
2345  case wasm::kI32:
2346  case wasm::kI64:
2347  case wasm::kF16:
2348  case wasm::kF32:
2349  case wasm::kF64:
2350  case wasm::kS128: {
2351  if (!snapshot_->capture_numeric_value()) continue;
2352  std::string value_string = obj->GetFieldValue(i).to_string();
2353  const char* value_name = names_->GetCopy(value_string.c_str());
2354  SnapshotObjectId id = heap_object_map_->get_next_id();
2355  HeapEntry* child_entry =
2356  snapshot_->AddEntry(HeapEntry::kString, value_name, id, 0, 0);
2357  entry->SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::kInternal, field_name,
2358  child_entry, generator_);
2359  break;
2360  }
2361  case wasm::kRef:
2362  case wasm::kRefNull: {
2363  int field_offset = type->field_offset(i);
2364  Tagged<Object> value = obj->RawField(field_offset).load(isolate);
2365  // We could consider hiding {null} fields by default (like we do for
2366  // arrays, see below), but for now we always include them, in the hope
2367  // that they might help identify opportunities for struct size
2368  // reductions.
2369  HeapEntry* value_entry = GetEntry(value);
2370  entry->SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::kProperty, field_name,
2371  value_entry, generator_);

2373  break;
2374  }

2376  case wasm::kTop:
2377  case wasm::kBottom:

2383 void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractWasmArrayReferences(Tagged<WasmArray> obj,

2499 class RootsReferencesExtractor : public RootVisitor {
2500  public:
2501  explicit RootsReferencesExtractor(V8HeapExplorer* explorer)
2502  : explorer_(explorer), visiting_weak_roots_(false) {}
2503 
2504  void SetVisitingWeakRoots() { visiting_weak_roots_ = true; }
2505 
2506  void VisitRootPointer(Root root, const char* description,
2507  FullObjectSlot p) override {
2508  Tagged<Object> object = *p;
2509 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_HANDLE
2510  if (object.ptr() == kTaggedNullAddress) return;
2511 #endif
2512  if (root == Root::kBuiltins) {
2513  explorer_->TagBuiltinCodeObject(Cast<Code>(object), description);
2514  }
2515  explorer_->SetGcSubrootReference(root, description, visiting_weak_roots_,
2516  object);
2517  }
2518 
2519  void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
2520  FullObjectSlot start, FullObjectSlot end) override {
2521  for (FullObjectSlot p = start; p < end; ++p) {
2522  DCHECK(!MapWord::IsPacked(p.Relaxed_Load().ptr()));
2523  VisitRootPointer(root, description, p);
2524  }
2525  }
2526 
2527  void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
2528  OffHeapObjectSlot start,
2529  OffHeapObjectSlot end) override {
2530  DCHECK_EQ(root, Root::kStringTable);
2531  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(explorer_->heap_->isolate());
2532  for (OffHeapObjectSlot p = start; p < end; ++p) {
2533  explorer_->SetGcSubrootReference(root, description, visiting_weak_roots_,
2534  p.load(cage_base));
2535  }
2536  }
2537 
2538  // Keep this synced with
2539  // MarkCompactCollector::RootMarkingVisitor::VisitRunningCode.
2540  void VisitRunningCode(FullObjectSlot code_slot,
2541  FullObjectSlot istream_or_smi_zero_slot) final {
2542  Tagged<Object> istream_or_smi_zero = *istream_or_smi_zero_slot;
2543  if (istream_or_smi_zero != Smi::zero()) {
2544  Tagged<Code> code = Cast<Code>(*code_slot);
2545  code->IterateDeoptimizationLiterals(this);
2546  VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, istream_or_smi_zero_slot);
2547  }
2548  VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, code_slot);
2549  }
2550 
2551  private:
2552  V8HeapExplorer* explorer_;
2553  bool visiting_weak_roots_;
2554 };
2555 
2556 bool V8HeapExplorer::IterateAndExtractReferences(
2557  HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator) {
2558  generator_ = generator;
2559 
2560  // Create references to the synthetic roots.
2561  SetRootGcRootsReference();
2562  for (int root = 0; root < static_cast<int>(Root::kNumberOfRoots); root++) {
2563  SetGcRootsReference(static_cast<Root>(root));
2564  }
2565 
2566  // Make sure builtin code objects get their builtin tags
2567  // first. Otherwise a particular JSFunction object could set
2568  // its custom name to a generic builtin.
2569  RootsReferencesExtractor extractor(this);
2570  ReadOnlyRoots(heap_).Iterate(&extractor);
2571  heap_->IterateRoots(
2572  &extractor,
2573  base::EnumSet<SkipRoot>{SkipRoot::kWeak, SkipRoot::kTracedHandles});
2574  // TODO(v8:11800): The heap snapshot generator incorrectly considers the weak
2575  // string tables as strong retainers. Move IterateWeakRoots after
2576  // SetVisitingWeakRoots.
2577  heap_->IterateWeakRoots(&extractor, {});
2578  extractor.SetVisitingWeakRoots();
2579  heap_->IterateWeakGlobalHandles(&extractor);
2580 
2581  bool interrupted = false;
2582 
2583  CombinedHeapObjectIterator iterator(heap_);
2584  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(heap_->isolate());
2585  // Heap iteration need not be finished but progress reporting may depend on
2586  // it being finished.
2587  for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj = iterator.Next(); !obj.is_null();
2588  obj = iterator.Next(), progress_->ProgressStep()) {
2589  if (interrupted) continue;
2590 
2591  max_pointers_ = obj->Size(cage_base) / kTaggedSize;
2592  if (max_pointers_ > visited_fields_.size()) {
2593  // Reallocate to right size.
2594  visited_fields_.resize(max_pointers_, false);
2595  }
2596 
2597 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_HEAP_SNAPSHOT_VERIFY
2598  std::unique_ptr<HeapEntryVerifier> verifier;
2599  // MarkingVisitorBase doesn't expect that we will ever visit read-only
2600  // objects, and fails DCHECKs if we attempt to. Read-only objects can
2601  // never retain read-write objects, so there is no risk in skipping
2602  // verification for them.
2603  if (v8_flags.heap_snapshot_verify &&
2604  !MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
2605  verifier = std::make_unique<HeapEntryVerifier>(generator, obj);
2606  }
2607 #endif
2608 
2609  HeapEntry* entry = GetEntry(obj);
2610  ExtractReferences(entry, obj);
2611  SetInternalReference(entry, "map", obj->map(cage_base),
2612  HeapObject::kMapOffset);
2613  // Extract unvisited fields as hidden references and restore tags
2614  // of visited fields.
2615  IndexedReferencesExtractor refs_extractor(this, obj, entry);
2616  VisitObject(heap_->isolate(), obj, &refs_extractor);
2617 
2618 #if DEBUG
2619  // Ensure visited_fields_ doesn't leak to the next object.
2620  for (size_t i = 0; i < max_pointers_; ++i) {
2621  DCHECK(!visited_fields_[i]);
2622  }
2623 #endif // DEBUG
2624 
2625  // Extract location for specific object types
2626  ExtractLocation(entry, obj);
2627 
2628  if (!progress_->ProgressReport(false)) interrupted = true;
2629  }
2630 
2631  generator_ = nullptr;
2632  return interrupted ? false : progress_->ProgressReport(true);
2633 }

2635 bool V8HeapExplorer::IsEssentialObject(Tagged<Object> object) {
2636  if (!IsHeapObject(object)) return false;
2637  // Avoid comparing objects in other pointer compression cages to objects
2638  // inside the main cage as the comparison may only look at the lower 32 bits.
2639  if (HeapLayout::InCodeSpace(Cast<HeapObject>(object)) ||
2640  HeapLayout::InTrustedSpace(Cast<HeapObject>(object))) {
2641  return true;
2642  }
2643  Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
2644  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2645  return !IsOddball(object, isolate) && object != roots.the_hole_value() &&
2646  object != roots.empty_byte_array() &&
2647  object != roots.empty_fixed_array() &&
2648  object != roots.empty_weak_fixed_array() &&
2649  object != roots.empty_descriptor_array() &&
2650  object != roots.fixed_array_map() && object != roots.cell_map() &&
2651  object != roots.global_property_cell_map() &&
2652  object != roots.shared_function_info_map() &&
2653  object != roots.free_space_map() &&
2654  object != roots.one_pointer_filler_map() &&
2655  object != roots.two_pointer_filler_map();
2656 }

2658 bool V8HeapExplorer::IsEssentialHiddenReference(Tagged<Object> parent,
2659  int field_offset) {
2660  if (IsAllocationSite(parent) &&
2661  field_offset == offsetof(AllocationSiteWithWeakNext, weak_next_))
2662  return false;
2663  if (IsContext(parent) &&
2664  field_offset == Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::NEXT_CONTEXT_LINK))
2665  return false;
2666  if (IsJSFinalizationRegistry(parent) &&
2667  field_offset == JSFinalizationRegistry::kNextDirtyOffset)
2668  return false;
2669  return true;
2670 }

2709 void V8HeapExplorer::SetInternalReference(HeapEntry* parent_entry,
2710  const char* reference_name,
2711  Tagged<Object> child_obj,

2835 void V8HeapExplorer::SetGcSubrootReference(Root root, const char* description,
2836  bool is_weak,
2837  Tagged<Object> child_obj) {
2838  if (IsSmi(child_obj)) {
2839  // TODO(arenevier): if we handle smis here, the snapshot gets 2 to 3 times
2840  // slower on large heaps. According to perf, The bulk of the extra works
2841  // happens in TemplateHashMapImpl::Probe method, when tyring to get
2842  // names->GetFormatted("%d / %s", index, description)
2843  return;
2844  }
2845  HeapEntry* child_entry = GetEntry(child_obj);
2846  if (child_entry == nullptr) return;
2847  auto child_heap_obj = Cast<HeapObject>(child_obj);
2848  const char* name = GetStrongGcSubrootName(child_heap_obj);
2849  HeapGraphEdge::Type edge_type =
2850  is_weak ? HeapGraphEdge::kWeak : HeapGraphEdge::kInternal;
2851  if (name != nullptr) {
2852  snapshot_->gc_subroot(root)->SetNamedReference(edge_type, name, child_entry,
2853  generator_);
2854  } else {
2855  snapshot_->gc_subroot(root)->SetNamedAutoIndexReference(
2856  edge_type, description, child_entry, names_, generator_);
2857  }
2858 
2859  // For full heap snapshots we do not emit user roots but rather rely on
2860  // regular GC roots to retain objects.
2861  if (snapshot_->expose_internals()) return;
2862 
2863  // Add a shortcut to JS global object reference at snapshot root.
2864  // That allows the user to easily find global objects. They are
2865  // also used as starting points in distance calculations.
2866  if (is_weak || !IsNativeContext(child_heap_obj)) return;
2867 
2868  Tagged<JSGlobalObject> global =
2869  Cast<Context>(child_heap_obj)->global_object();
2870  if (!IsJSGlobalObject(global)) return;
2871 
2872  if (!user_roots_.insert(global).second) return;
2873 
2874  SetUserGlobalReference(global);
2875 }

2877 const char* V8HeapExplorer::GetStrongGcSubrootName(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
2878  if (strong_gc_subroot_names_.empty()) {
2879  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::FromHeap(heap_);
2880  for (RootIndex root_index = RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot;
2881  root_index <= RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot; ++root_index) {
2882  const char* name = RootsTable::name(root_index);
2883  Tagged<Object> root = isolate->root(root_index);
2884  CHECK(!IsSmi(root));
2885  strong_gc_subroot_names_.emplace(Cast<HeapObject>(root), name);
2886  }
2887  CHECK(!strong_gc_subroot_names_.empty());

2907 void V8HeapExplorer::RecursivelyTagConstantPool(Tagged<Object> obj,
2908  const char* tag,
2909  HeapEntry::Type type,
2910  int recursion_limit) {
2911  --recursion_limit;
2912  if (IsFixedArrayExact(obj, isolate())) {
2913  Tagged<FixedArray> arr = Cast<FixedArray>(obj);
2914  TagObject(arr, tag, type);
2915  if (recursion_limit <= 0) return;
2916  for (int i = 0; i < arr->length(); ++i) {
2917  RecursivelyTagConstantPool(arr->get(i), tag, type, recursion_limit);
2918  }
2919  } else if (IsTrustedFixedArray(obj, isolate())) {
2920  Tagged<TrustedFixedArray> arr = Cast<TrustedFixedArray>(obj);
2921  TagObject(arr, tag, type, /*overwrite_existing_name=*/true);
2922  if (recursion_limit <= 0) return;
2923  for (int i = 0; i < arr->length(); ++i) {
2924  RecursivelyTagConstantPool(arr->get(i), tag, type, recursion_limit);
2925  }
2926  } else if (IsNameDictionary(obj, isolate()) ||
2927  IsNumberDictionary(obj, isolate())) {
2928  TagObject(obj, tag, type);
2929  }
2930 }

2933  public:

2936  : isolate_(isolate), handler_(handler) {}

2939  FullObjectSlot start, FullObjectSlot end) override {
2940  VisitRootPointersImpl(root, description, start, end);

2942 
2943  void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,

2945  OffHeapObjectSlot end) override {
2946  VisitRootPointersImpl(root, description, start, end);

2951  void VisitRootPointersImpl(Root root, const char* description, TSlot start,
2952  TSlot end) {

2954  DCHECK(!MapWord::IsPacked(p.Relaxed_Load(isolate_).ptr()));

2960  if (!IsJSGlobalObject(global, isolate_)) continue;
2961  handler_(handle(Cast<JSGlobalObject>(global), isolate_));
2962  }
2963  }
2964 
2965  Isolate* isolate_;
2966  std::function<void(Handle<JSGlobalObject>)> handler_;

3107 HeapEntry* EmbedderGraphEntriesAllocator::AllocateEntry(HeapThing ptr) {
3108  EmbedderGraphImpl::Node* node =
3109  reinterpret_cast<EmbedderGraphImpl::Node*>(ptr);
3110  DCHECK(node->IsEmbedderNode());
3111  size_t size = node->SizeInBytes();
3112  Address lookup_address = reinterpret_cast<Address>(node->GetNativeObject());
3113  HeapObjectsMap::MarkEntryAccessed accessed =
3114  HeapObjectsMap::MarkEntryAccessed::kYes;
3115  HeapObjectsMap::IsNativeObject is_native_object =
3116  HeapObjectsMap::IsNativeObject::kNo;
3117  if (!lookup_address) {
3118  // If there is not a native object associated with this embedder object,
3119  // then request the address of the embedder object.
3120  lookup_address = reinterpret_cast<Address>(node->GetAddress());
3121  is_native_object = HeapObjectsMap::IsNativeObject::kYes;
3122  }
3123  if (!lookup_address) {
3124  // If the Node implementation did not provide either a native address or an
3125  // embedder address, then use the address of the Node itself for the lookup.
3126  // In this case, we'll set the "accessed" flag on the newly created
3127  // HeapEntry to false, to indicate that this entry should not persist for
3128  // future snapshots.
3129  lookup_address = reinterpret_cast<Address>(node);
3130  accessed = HeapObjectsMap::MarkEntryAccessed::kNo;
3131  }
3132  SnapshotObjectId id = heap_object_map_->FindOrAddEntry(
3133  lookup_address, 0, accessed, is_native_object);
3134  auto* heap_entry = snapshot_->AddEntry(EmbedderGraphNodeType(node),
3135  EmbedderGraphNodeName(names_, node),
3136  id, static_cast<int>(size), 0);
3137  heap_entry->set_detachedness(node->GetDetachedness());
3138  return heap_entry;
3139 }

3156 void NativeObjectsExplorer::MergeNodeIntoEntry(
3157  HeapEntry* entry, EmbedderGraph::Node* original_node,
3158  EmbedderGraph::Node* wrapper_node) {
3159  // The wrapper node may be an embedder node (for testing purposes) or a V8
3160  // node (production code).
3161  if (!wrapper_node->IsEmbedderNode()) {
3162  // For V8 nodes only we can add a lookup.
3163  EmbedderGraphImpl::V8NodeImpl* v8_node =
3164  static_cast<EmbedderGraphImpl::V8NodeImpl*>(wrapper_node);
3165  Tagged<Object> object = v8_node->GetObject();

3167  if (original_node->GetNativeObject()) {
3168  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
3169  heap_object_map_->AddMergedNativeEntry(original_node->GetNativeObject(),
3170  heap_object.address());
3171  DCHECK_EQ(entry->id(), heap_object_map_->FindMergedNativeEntry(
3172  original_node->GetNativeObject()));
3173  }
3174  }
3175  entry->set_detachedness(original_node->GetDetachedness());
3176  entry->set_name(MergeNames(
3177  names_, EmbedderGraphNodeName(names_, original_node), entry->name()));
3178  entry->set_type(EmbedderGraphNodeType(original_node));
3179  DCHECK_GE(entry->self_size() + original_node->SizeInBytes(),
3180  entry->self_size());
3181  entry->add_self_size(original_node->SizeInBytes());
3182 }

3184 HeapEntry* NativeObjectsExplorer::EntryForEmbedderGraphNode(
3185  EmbedderGraphImpl::Node* node) {
3186  // Return the entry for the wrapper node if present.
3187  if (node->WrapperNode()) {
3188  node = node->WrapperNode();
3189  }

3195  // Node is V8NodeImpl.
3196  Tagged<Object> object =
3197  static_cast<EmbedderGraphImpl::V8NodeImpl*>(node)->GetObject();
3198  if (IsSmi(object)) return nullptr;
3199  auto* entry = generator_->FindEntry(

3204 bool NativeObjectsExplorer::IterateAndExtractReferences(
3205  HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator) {
3206  generator_ = generator;
3207 
3208  if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_use_embedder_graph &&
3209  snapshot_->profiler()->HasBuildEmbedderGraphCallback()) {
3210  v8::HandleScope scope(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate_));
3211  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3212  EmbedderGraphImpl graph;
3213  snapshot_->profiler()->BuildEmbedderGraph(
3214  isolate_, &graph, generator_->TakeCppHeapExternalObjects());
3215  for (const auto& node : graph.nodes()) {
3216  // Only add embedder nodes as V8 nodes have been added already by the
3217  // V8HeapExplorer.
3218  if (!node->IsEmbedderNode()) continue;
3219 
3220  if (auto* entry = EntryForEmbedderGraphNode(node.get())) {
3221  if (node->IsRootNode()) {
3222  snapshot_->root()->SetIndexedAutoIndexReference(
3223  HeapGraphEdge::kElement, entry, generator_,
3224  HeapEntry::kOffHeapPointer);
3225  }
3226  if (node->WrapperNode()) {
3227  MergeNodeIntoEntry(entry, node.get(), node->WrapperNode());
3228  }
3229  }
3230  }
3231  // Fill edges of the graph.
3232  for (const auto& edge : graph.edges()) {
3233  // |from| and |to| can be nullptr if the corresponding node is a V8 node
3234  // pointing to a Smi.
3235  HeapEntry* from = EntryForEmbedderGraphNode(edge.from);
3236  if (!from) continue;
3237  HeapEntry* to = EntryForEmbedderGraphNode(edge.to);
3238  if (!to) continue;
3239  if (edge.name == nullptr) {
3240  from->SetIndexedAutoIndexReference(HeapGraphEdge::kElement, to,
3241  generator_,
3242  HeapEntry::kOffHeapPointer);
3243  } else {
3244  from->SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::kInternal,
3245  names_->GetCopy(edge.name), to, generator_,
3246  HeapEntry::kOffHeapPointer);
3247  }
3248  }
3249  snapshot_->set_extra_native_bytes(graph.native_size());
3250  }
3251  generator_ = nullptr;
3252  return true;
3253 }

3281 bool HeapSnapshotGenerator::GenerateSnapshot() {
3282  v8::base::ElapsedTimer timer;
3283  timer.Start();
3284 
3285  IsolateSafepointScope scope(heap_);
3286 
3287  Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
3288  auto temporary_global_object_tags =
3289  v8_heap_explorer_.CollectTemporaryGlobalObjectsTags();
3290 
3291  EmbedderStackStateScope stack_scope(
3292  heap_, EmbedderStackStateOrigin::kImplicitThroughTask, stack_state_);
3293  heap_->CollectAllAvailableGarbage(GarbageCollectionReason::kHeapProfiler);
3294  heap_->CompleteSweepingFull();
3295 
3296  // No allocation that could trigger GC from here onwards. We cannot use a
3297  // DisallowGarbageCollection scope as the HeapObjectIterator used during
3298  // snapshot creation enters a safepoint as well. However, in practice we
3299  // already enter a safepoint above so that should never trigger a GC.
3300  DisallowPositionInfoSlow no_position_info_slow;
3301 
3302  NullContextForSnapshotScope null_context_scope(isolate);
3303 
3304  v8_heap_explorer_.MakeGlobalObjectTagMap(
3305  std::move(temporary_global_object_tags));
3306 
3307  InitProgressCounter();
3308 
3309  snapshot_->AddSyntheticRootEntries();
3310 
3311  v8_heap_explorer_.PopulateLineEnds();
3312  if (!FillReferences()) return false;
3313 
3314  snapshot_->FillChildren();
3315  snapshot_->RememberLastJSObjectId();
3316 
3317  progress_counter_ = progress_total_;
3318 
3319  if (i::v8_flags.profile_heap_snapshot) {
3320  base::OS::PrintError("[Heap snapshot took %0.3f ms]\n",
3321  timer.Elapsed().InMillisecondsF());
3322  }
3323  timer.Stop();
3324  if (!ProgressReport(true)) return false;
3325  return true;
3326 }
3327 
3328 bool HeapSnapshotGenerator::GenerateSnapshotAfterGC() {
3329  // Same as above, but no allocations, no GC run, and no progress report.
3330  IsolateSafepointScope scope(heap_);
3331  auto temporary_global_object_tags =
3332  v8_heap_explorer_.CollectTemporaryGlobalObjectsTags();
3333  NullContextForSnapshotScope null_context_scope(heap_->isolate());
3334  v8_heap_explorer_.MakeGlobalObjectTagMap(
3335  std::move(temporary_global_object_tags));
3336  snapshot_->AddSyntheticRootEntries();
3337  v8_heap_explorer_.PopulateLineEnds();
3338  if (!FillReferences()) return false;
3339  snapshot_->FillChildren();
3340  snapshot_->RememberLastJSObjectId();
3341  return true;
3342 }

3344 void HeapSnapshotGenerator::ProgressStep() {
3345  // Only increment the progress_counter_ until
3346  // equal to progress_total -1 == progress_counter.
3347  // This ensures that intermediate ProgressReport calls will never signal
3348  // that the work is finished (i.e. progress_counter_ == progress_total_).
3349  // Only the forced ProgressReport() at the end of GenerateSnapshot() should,
3350  // after setting progress_counter_ = progress_total_, signal that the
3351  // work is finished because signalling finished twice
3352  // breaks the DevTools frontend.
3353  if (control_ != nullptr && progress_total_ > progress_counter_ + 1) {
3354  ++progress_counter_;
3355  }
3356 }

3358 bool HeapSnapshotGenerator::ProgressReport(bool force) {
3359  const int kProgressReportGranularity = 10000;
3360  if (control_ != nullptr &&
3361  (force || progress_counter_ % kProgressReportGranularity == 0)) {
3362  return control_->ReportProgressValue(progress_counter_, progress_total_) ==
3363  v8::ActivityControl::kContinue;
3364  }
3365  return true;
3366 }

3684 void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeString(const unsigned char* s) {
3685  writer_->AddCharacter('\"');
3686  for (; *s != '\0'; ++s) {
3687  switch (*s) {
3688  case '\b':
3689  writer_->AddString("\\b");
3690  continue;
3691  case '\f':
3692  writer_->AddString("\\f");
3693  continue;
3694  case '\n':
3695  writer_->AddString("\\n");
3696  continue;
3697  case '\r':
3698  writer_->AddString("\\r");
3699  continue;
3700  case '\t':
3701  writer_->AddString("\\t");
3702  continue;
3703  case '\"':
3704  case '\\':
3705  writer_->AddCharacter('\\');
3706  writer_->AddCharacter(*s);
3707  continue;
3708  default:
3709  if (*s > 31 && *s < 128) {
3710  writer_->AddCharacter(*s);
3711  } else if (*s <= 31) {
3712  // Special character with no dedicated literal.
3713  WriteUChar(writer_, *s);
3714  } else {
3715  // Convert UTF-8 into \u UTF-16 literal.
3716  size_t length = 1, cursor = 0;
3717  for (; length <= 4 && *(s + length) != '\0'; ++length) {
3718  }
3719  unibrow::uchar c = unibrow::Utf8::CalculateValue(s, length, &cursor);
3720  if (c != unibrow::Utf8::kBadChar) {
3721  WriteUChar(writer_, c);
3722  DCHECK_NE(cursor, 0);
3723  s += cursor - 1;
3724  } else {
3725  writer_->AddCharacter('?');
3726  }
3727  }
3728  }
3729  }
3730  writer_->AddCharacter('\"');
3731 }
